title: Bad MIR when casting a reference to dyn*

labels.name: I-ICE
labels.description: Issue: The compiler panicked, giving an Internal Compilation Error (ICE) ❄️

labels.name: T-compiler
labels.description: Relevant to the compiler team, which will review and decide on the PR/issue.

labels.name: requires-nightly
labels.description: This issue requires a nightly compiler in some way.

body:
Test case ([playground](https://play.rust-lang.org/?version=nightly&mode=debug&edition=2021&gist=a0b4dd20321aed6d5180190d9b2ed3b0):
```rust
#![feature(dyn_star)]
#![allow(incomplete_features)]

trait AddOne {
    fn add1(&mut self) -> usize;
}

impl AddOne for usize {
    fn add1(&mut self) -> usize {
        *self += 1;
        *self
    }
}

impl AddOne for &mut usize {
    fn add1(&mut self) -> usize {
        (*self).add1()
    }
}

fn add_one(mut i: dyn* AddOne) -> usize {
    i.add1()
}

fn main() {
    let mut x = 42;
    let y = &mut x as dyn* AddOne;

    println!("{}", add_one(y));
}
```
